snippet: The 1918 Cadillac Type 57 of John H. Denison, which served in World War I, is the latest addition to the National Historic Vehicle Register.
abstract: National Historic Vehicle Register, managed by Historic Vehicle Association in collaboration with Interior Department, creates a permanent archive of historic automobiles within the Library of Congress; latest addition to register is 1918 Cadillac Type 57 owned by John H Denison and put into service in Europe in World War I.
lead_paragraph: The 1918 Cadillac Type 57 of John H. Denison, which served in World War I, is the latest addition to the National Historic Vehicle Register.
